1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,167
[SCREAMS]

2
00:00:01,333 --> 00:00:05,367
- [LUNA CHUCKLES]
- [SINGING "HAPPY BIRTHDAY"]

3
00:00:05,633 --> 00:00:08,033
<i> Happy birthday...</i>

4
00:00:08,167 --> 00:00:09,733
She was okay when we first met.

5
00:00:09,833 --> 00:00:11,300
<i> But suddenly, she left me.</i>

6
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:12,900
<i> And now, she's ignoring me.</i>

7
00:00:13,233 --> 00:00:14,133
<i> You still love her.</i>

8
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:16,367
<i>Find all the answers
to your questions.</i>

9
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:18,300
<i>Are you the ones
who need to break the curse?</i>

10
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:19,633
<i> I'm not included, mister!</i>

11
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:20,700
<i>- Just them.
- Ouch!</i>

12
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:21,633
<i>- Just them!
- N-No.</i>

13
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:22,867
<i> Mister?</i>

14
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,300
<i>Mister, what are you
going to do?</i>

15
00:00:24,467 --> 00:00:25,867
<i> I'm going to break your curse!</i>

16
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:26,900
<i>- No!
- No!</i>

17
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,233
<i> Come in.</i>

18
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:31,400
<i>I'm all for it, and she's good
for the business...</i>

19
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:34,267
<i>She's good for
our family, and, uh...</i>

20
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:36,333
<i>Most importantly,
she's good for your heart.</i>

21
00:00:36,633 --> 00:00:38,500
<i>Seems like this isn't
your first time, huh?</i>

22
00:00:38,633 --> 00:00:40,600
<i>This feels like a facial
treatment at a salon, Kiko.</i>

23
00:00:41,967 --> 00:00:44,300
Mister, what is the smoke
treatment for?

24
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,300
What did you say?

25
00:00:46,467 --> 00:00:47,333
I'm not impulsive.

26
00:00:47,467 --> 00:00:50,467
Ah, the smoke, mister.
What is it for?

27
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:52,333
Ah, the smoke.

28
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:55,833
Oh, it's for temporarily
removing bad luck.

29
00:00:56,533 --> 00:00:59,000
So it's confirmed, mister?

30
00:00:59,133 --> 00:01:01,267
We really do have bad luck?

31
00:01:01,367 --> 00:01:04,267
Yes. For the bad luck
to completely disappear,

32
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:07,133
you need to climb
Mount Kusama

33
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:10,133
and perform a ritual.

34
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:11,967
A ritual?

35
00:01:12,133 --> 00:01:13,633
Wait, what ritual?

36
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:16,167
A cleansing ritual.

37
00:01:16,333 --> 00:01:20,000
On the thirteenth Friday.

38
00:01:20,167 --> 00:01:23,333
As the sun sets.

39
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:25,700
Oh, that's it?

40
00:01:26,367 --> 00:01:28,167
What do you mean, "that's it"?

41
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:30,167
Kiko, hiking isn't easy.

42
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:31,533
Then I'll just do it myself.

43
00:01:31,667 --> 00:01:34,300
It can't be just you.
It has to be both of you.

44
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:38,100
And you must not tell
anyone about this.

45
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:41,167
In short, it's a secret.

46
00:01:41,367 --> 00:01:46,500
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

47
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:50,467
[HUMMING]

48
00:01:51,367 --> 00:01:54,633
[HUMMING CONTINUES]

49
00:01:55,767 --> 00:02:00,667
[HUMMING CONTINUES]

50
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:04,500
There...

51
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:08,567
You'll wear those when
you climb Mount Kusama.

52
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:13,733
Those are part of your ritual.

53
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:19,400
[HUMMING]

54
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:30,000
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,300
Anything, bro?
[TAPS SHOULDER]

56
00:03:24,467 --> 00:03:25,733
On the house.

57
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:26,800
[CHUCKLES]

58
00:03:27,467 --> 00:03:29,233
Don't get too happy yet, bro.

59
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:30,900
It's still too early.

60
00:03:31,667 --> 00:03:32,467
Whiskey?

61
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:34,767
Sure, I'm game.

62
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:36,100
Marvin, two.

63
00:03:38,133 --> 00:03:39,300
You know,

64
00:03:39,467 --> 00:03:41,267
you already got Uncle Ronald
to agree to a meeting.

65
00:03:41,433 --> 00:03:43,133
That's all I needed.

66
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:45,267
I'll take care of getting
him to say yes.

67
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:46,833
But you need a date.

68
00:03:47,767 --> 00:03:48,967
A date?

69
00:03:49,133 --> 00:03:50,300
For your dad?

70
00:03:50,467 --> 00:03:52,133
Wait, does your mom know that?

71
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:53,767
Not for my dad!

72
00:03:55,033 --> 00:03:56,600
A date for you.

73
00:03:56,700 --> 00:04:00,933
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

74
00:04:01,033 --> 00:04:03,367
Well, I can bring Trixie.

75
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:07,933
You know my dad.

76
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:11,200
- A traditional businessman.
- Oh?

77
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:12,800
Do you know how he sees you?

78
00:04:14,233 --> 00:04:17,033
You are not
a stable businessman.

79
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,833
Because you don't have
a girlfriend.

80
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,800
What does that have
to do with anything?

81
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:23,667
For him,

82
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:26,600
if you can commit
to a relationship,

83
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:29,933
then you can give the same
loyalty and commitment

84
00:04:30,067 --> 00:04:31,067
to a business.

85
00:04:33,667 --> 00:04:35,067
Wait, so you're telling me,

86
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:38,033
I need a girlfriend to do
business with Uncle Ronald?

87
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,667
[CHUCKLES]

88
00:04:41,367 --> 00:04:43,333
A leave of absence?!

89
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:45,167
From our lunch
and coffee updates?

90
00:04:45,267 --> 00:04:46,367
[CLEARS THROAT]

91
00:04:47,067 --> 00:04:48,333
Yes.

92
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:49,667
[SCOFFS]

93
00:04:50,667 --> 00:04:52,500
- Why?
- [INHALES]

94
00:04:53,733 --> 00:04:55,733
I just have something
I need to take care of.

95
00:04:57,533 --> 00:04:58,733
And what is that?

96
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:03,200
It's not part of our deal

97
00:05:03,367 --> 00:05:06,367
for you to know
every detail of my life.

98
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:07,567
Right?

99
00:05:07,733 --> 00:05:10,033
That's why it's called
coffee updates, right?

100
00:05:10,133 --> 00:05:12,367
Just the things I want
to share with you.

101
00:05:12,533 --> 00:05:13,867
If you force me,

102
00:05:14,033 --> 00:05:16,333
then it's like you're
controlling my life, right?

103
00:05:16,433 --> 00:05:18,233
And that's not part
of your wishes.

104
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,567
[EXHALES]

105
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:22,067
You're just running away.

106
00:05:22,233 --> 00:05:23,100
Mm.

107
00:05:23,233 --> 00:05:25,400
I'll complete my one month.

108
00:05:25,567 --> 00:05:27,867
And the days I missed,

109
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:32,333
I will fulfill them
until I complete 30 days.

110
00:05:32,433 --> 00:05:34,033
Oh...

111
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,867
So...

112
00:05:36,067 --> 00:05:37,533
it can be extended?

113
00:05:38,267 --> 00:05:39,600
Is that what you're saying?

114
00:05:40,267 --> 00:05:41,533
Yes.

115
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:45,267
You're thinking
like a businessman.

116
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:50,633
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

117
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:51,767
Deal!

118
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:53,800
Cheers?

119
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,467
- Cheers.
- [GLASSES CLINK]

120
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:02,733
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

121
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:05,733
Ten-minute coffee update
is over.

122
00:06:06,767 --> 00:06:07,767
Bye!

123
00:06:14,767 --> 00:06:18,900
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

124
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,967
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

125
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:23,000
It would've been better
if it were a girlfriend.

126
00:06:23,767 --> 00:06:25,967
A date? That'll do.

127
00:06:27,133 --> 00:06:29,600
Where am I even going
to find a date like that?

128
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:32,567
Sir.

129
00:06:32,667 --> 00:06:35,267
Sir, I just need your signature.

130
00:06:35,367 --> 00:06:36,433
Okay. Give it to me.

131
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:43,600
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

132
00:06:54,967 --> 00:06:56,367
[JUSTIN]<i> Why is Leon
</i> always like that?

133
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:58,133
It's like he's hiding something.

134
00:06:58,233 --> 00:07:00,500
- [JUSTIN]<i> What's that?
</i>- [LEON] Uh, nothing.

135
00:07:00,667 --> 00:07:02,500
<i> Just business contracts.</i>

136
00:07:02,967 --> 00:07:03,933
<i> Can I see?</i>

137
00:07:04,033 --> 00:07:05,300
<i> Why?!</i>

138
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,633
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

139
00:07:06,733 --> 00:07:07,833
<i> Just checking something.</i>

140
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,600
<i>- Dad's business transactions.
- Did you find it?</i>

141
00:07:10,700 --> 00:07:12,500
<i>- I can help you.
- No.</i>

142
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:14,267
<i> I already found it.</i>

143
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:21,300
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

144
00:07:31,433 --> 00:07:33,000
[TRIXIE] Oh my god.

145
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,667
Hey, baby girl!

146
00:07:37,433 --> 00:07:39,167
You're following me, huh?

147
00:07:39,267 --> 00:07:41,167
- I'm not.
- [JUSTIN] Hey--

148
00:07:41,267 --> 00:07:43,300
You can admit it.
It's fine.

149
00:07:46,533 --> 00:07:48,233
What are you looking at?

150
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:49,533
Everything.

151
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:50,767
Why?

152
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:53,433
I'm buying it.

153
00:07:53,567 --> 00:07:55,567
Nice! I can help you.

154
00:07:55,733 --> 00:07:57,333
No, thank you.

155
00:07:57,433 --> 00:07:58,900
You don't want to? Why not?

156
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:02,733
I said no, right?
You're so persistent.

157
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:05,900
I'm the one offering help,
and you're acting like that?

158
00:08:06,067 --> 00:08:07,833
- You know what, it's because--
- [SPLASHES]

159
00:08:07,933 --> 00:08:09,367
Sorry, sorry, sorry, sorry.

160
00:08:09,467 --> 00:08:10,767
- Justin!
- I didn't mean to.

161
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:11,900
It's fine, you're still pretty--

162
00:08:12,067 --> 00:08:14,433
Can you just
stop bothering me?!

163
00:08:14,567 --> 00:08:16,033
You're such a mess, Justin!

164
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:18,533
I already said sorry.
I'll make it up to you.

165
00:08:18,633 --> 00:08:20,267
- I will help you with--
- Look!

166
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,700
I don't need your help!

167
00:08:23,433 --> 00:08:24,400
Okay?!

168
00:08:25,767 --> 00:08:27,067
What do you not get about it?

169
00:08:27,233 --> 00:08:29,533
You can't even do your job
properly at Hotel 88,

170
00:08:29,633 --> 00:08:31,100
and you want to help me?!

171
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:35,233
You're always chasing women,
drinking, going out!

172
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:36,967
That's your whole life, right?

173
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:39,733
You're the most useless one
in your family!

174
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:46,233
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

175
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,067
That was harsh.

176
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:51,867
You don't even know me
that well.

177
00:08:51,967 --> 00:08:54,800
And I don't need to get
to know you more, Justin.

178
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:55,933
Okay?

179
00:08:56,633 --> 00:08:58,233
So leave me the hell alone!

180
00:08:58,333 --> 00:08:59,900
I'm a businesswoman.

181
00:09:00,633 --> 00:09:02,833
I can do this on my own.
I don't need you.

182
00:09:03,967 --> 00:09:11,067
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:09:17,967 --> 00:09:20,100
I can't get proper rest.

184
00:09:20,267 --> 00:09:22,800
Oh, why, ma'am?
Is the air conditioner broken?

185
00:09:22,967 --> 00:09:24,900
- We'll send someone--
- No.

186
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,467
There's a foul smell.

187
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:27,900
Hmm?

188
00:09:28,033 --> 00:09:29,467
[MONETTE]
Uh, what kind of smell?

189
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:32,833
From the bathroom?

190
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:33,767
No.

191
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:35,800
Not inside my room either.

192
00:09:35,967 --> 00:09:37,800
It's coming from outside,
but I can't tell where.

193
00:09:37,967 --> 00:09:39,300
It smells like...

194
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:40,367
It smells like something dead.

195
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:43,133
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

196
00:09:43,233 --> 00:09:44,300
Dead?

197
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:52,800
[EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES]

198
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,300
[COUGHING]

199
00:09:57,333 --> 00:10:00,133
Ugh! The guest was right.

200
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:01,800
It smells like something dead!

201
00:10:01,933 --> 00:10:03,667
Like rotting meat or something.

202
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:06,233
I wonder what it is.

203
00:10:06,667 --> 00:10:09,567
We need to get rid of it.
What if the guests check out?

204
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:12,367
Let's just follow the smell.

205
00:10:12,367 --> 00:10:13,833
[SNIFFS] Gosh.

206
00:10:13,833 --> 00:10:17,833
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

207
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:20,200
[COUGHING]

208
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:22,167
[LUNA] They're looking
for a date?

209
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:24,300
Yes, ma'am.

210
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,067
A date for Martin.

211
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:29,133
What's the date for?

212
00:10:30,867 --> 00:10:32,300
[MARTIN] Sari!

213
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:36,300
I'll go now, Miss Luna.
Sir Martin's calling me.

214
00:10:36,533 --> 00:10:43,233
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

215
00:10:45,767 --> 00:10:47,533
What's the date for?

216
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:48,767
[MONETTE] My goodness.
[SNIFFS]

217
00:10:49,567 --> 00:10:53,300
[BREATHES DEEPLY, SNIFFLES]

218
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:55,900
- [RAT SQUEAKING]
- [SCREAMING] Aah!

219
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:59,567
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

220
00:10:59,567 --> 00:11:00,567
[GIO] It's gone!

221
00:11:00,567 --> 00:11:03,700
- Aah! [WHIMPERS]
- Calm down. It's gone now.

222
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:07,533
But it was as big
as a fetus, sir!

223
00:11:07,533 --> 00:11:09,667
It's alright now. Calm down.

224
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:13,700
- It stinks.
- [COUGHS]

225
00:11:15,933 --> 00:11:17,567
The smell's gotten worse.

226
00:11:18,267 --> 00:11:20,133
It doesn't go away.

227
00:11:20,133 --> 00:11:22,300
It's definitely coming
from here.

228
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:25,633
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

229
00:11:25,633 --> 00:11:27,900
Sir Gio, I think that's foul.

230
00:11:28,767 --> 00:11:30,267
I'm just making sure.

231
00:11:30,267 --> 00:11:31,433
The smell might not
be going away

232
00:11:31,433 --> 00:11:32,567
because it's coming
from one of us.

233
00:11:33,233 --> 00:11:35,333
And that's why you're
sniffing me?

234
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:36,600
Well, I'm sure it's not me.

235
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,933
Why aren't you sniffing Monette?

236
00:11:37,933 --> 00:11:39,900
For your information, I'm fresh.

237
00:11:42,667 --> 00:11:43,767
What is it?

238
00:11:45,433 --> 00:11:47,800
What happened?
Why were you screaming?

239
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:49,267
It stinks here.

240
00:11:49,267 --> 00:11:53,467
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

241
00:11:53,467 --> 00:11:54,600
What happened?

242
00:11:56,433 --> 00:11:57,467
[COUGHS]

243
00:11:57,933 --> 00:11:59,567
What's that smell?

244
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:04,267
We're looking for the source.
The guests are complaining.

245
00:12:06,633 --> 00:12:09,167
You guys can go.
Gio and I will look for it.

246
00:12:09,167 --> 00:12:12,800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

247
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:13,833
Ugh.

248
00:12:15,667 --> 00:12:16,700
[COUGHS]

249
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:18,600
It smells so bad.

250
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,167
[MONETTE COUGHS]

251
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:28,800
So, let's go?

252
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:43,633
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

253
00:12:53,667 --> 00:12:55,833
[COUGHING]

254
00:13:04,767 --> 00:13:06,833
You said there was
a big rat earlier.

255
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:11,400
Could the smell be coming
from a dead rat?

256
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:13,533
[SNIFFLES, COUGHS]

257
00:13:14,567 --> 00:13:17,333
Maybe, but it smells really bad.

258
00:13:21,267 --> 00:13:23,033
Is this an old basement?

259
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:29,533
Martin and Kiko inspected it
before the hotel opened.

260
00:13:31,733 --> 00:13:34,700
Monette said
it used to be a storage.

261
00:13:36,533 --> 00:13:38,733
Was it checked
before the hotel opened?

262
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:42,000
From what I know, it wasn't.

263
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:44,900
[COUGHS]

264
00:13:46,967 --> 00:13:48,533
Why was this off-limits?

265
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,600
[RATTLING]

266
00:13:55,733 --> 00:13:56,767
Did you hear that?

267
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,567
I think it came from over there.

268
00:13:59,567 --> 00:14:00,633
I'll go check.

269
00:14:01,433 --> 00:14:02,500
I'll check here too.

270
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:09,400
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

271
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:39,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:45,133
[CLANGING]

273
00:14:45,133 --> 00:14:47,967
[GIO BREATHING HEAVILY]

274
00:15:00,467 --> 00:15:07,333
[UNSETTLING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

275
00:15:08,867 --> 00:15:09,967
Aah!

276
00:15:12,667 --> 00:15:13,667
Gio?

277
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,367
[MARTIN] Gio?

278
00:15:21,067 --> 00:15:22,467
What happened?

279
00:15:23,967 --> 00:15:25,967
It was a cat.
I was just startled.

280
00:15:28,133 --> 00:15:30,600
[GIO] The smell earlier must've
really been a dead rat.

281
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:33,800
Let's go back upstairs.

282
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,567
[LEON] Let's just call someone
to check this place.

283
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:43,533
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

284
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:03,033
[WOMAN 1] So while we're
staying here, we'll wear a mask?

285
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:05,500
We're very sorry
for the inconvenience.

286
00:16:05,667 --> 00:16:07,833
[MARTIN] Due to unforeseen
events,

287
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:10,433
an animal unexpectedly
got inside.

288
00:16:10,467 --> 00:16:12,867
I mean, it's pretty obvious
because we're close to nature.

289
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:16,700
[WOMAN 2] If you knew about it,
you should've seen this coming.

290
00:16:18,367 --> 00:16:20,267
We're really sorry.

291
00:16:20,267 --> 00:16:22,567
For those of you who
booked around the area,

292
00:16:22,567 --> 00:16:24,200
your rooms are already ready.

293
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,367
[MARTIN] Rest assured

294
00:16:25,367 --> 00:16:27,800
that our front desk associates
will take care of you.

295
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:30,100
And we will give you
discounts for your stay.

296
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:31,767
[WOMAN 2] Good,
we deserve a discount.

297
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:34,400
- We're really sorry.
- We're so sorry.

298
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:35,733
- We're sorry.
- We're sorry.

299
00:16:35,733 --> 00:16:42,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

300
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,367
Discount?

301
00:16:46,267 --> 00:16:48,000
This will further reduce
the hotel's revenue.

302
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,767
You know how bad
online reviews are.

303
00:16:49,767 --> 00:16:51,500
Have you found a cleaner yet?

304
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:53,667
Yes. However, they are
unable to attend because

305
00:16:53,667 --> 00:16:55,900
they are not available.
They're fully booked.

306
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:58,667
I asked for other cleaners
but they weren't available.

307
00:16:58,667 --> 00:17:00,567
- They're available tomorrow.
- Tomorrow?!

308
00:17:00,567 --> 00:17:02,600
[LUNA] The odor must
be eliminated by tonight.

309
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:04,800
This might reach the municipal
hall or the tourism office.

310
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:06,333
They might think we're not
taking any action.

311
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:07,567
Fine.

312
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,500
I'll handle it.

313
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:13,600
- [LUNA] Is there no staff--
- Martin, where are the things?

314
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:16,333
- Caesar knows where.
- I'll just look for him.

315
00:17:16,367 --> 00:17:23,333
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

316
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:25,767
Luna.

317
00:17:32,700 --> 00:17:37,467
[WAVES CRASHING]

318
00:17:39,667 --> 00:17:41,633
[MONETTE] Sir, extra face mask.

319
00:17:41,633 --> 00:17:42,933
You may not handle the smell.

320
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:45,433
Thank you.

321
00:17:46,167 --> 00:17:49,333
Monette, has the basement been
left uncleaned for a while now?

322
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:52,500
It's been a long time
since that was checked.

323
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:54,633
Raphie, when was
the basement last checked?

324
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:58,600
I think it's been a while,
Sir Michael is still alive.

325
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,000
[MONETTE] I don't think so...

326
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,767
But we'll double-check it
with the cleaners.

327
00:18:05,867 --> 00:18:07,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

328
00:18:07,867 --> 00:18:09,700
[CHUCKLES]

329
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:11,500
Sis, you're losing it again.

330
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:14,000
No...

331
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,633
I just remember Sir Michael.

332
00:18:16,467 --> 00:18:19,167
He used to stay here
all the time.

333
00:18:19,167 --> 00:18:21,100
The breeze is refreshing.

334
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:24,833
- [SIGHS]
- I kinda miss Sir Michael.

335
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:26,367
Absolutely.

336
00:18:27,067 --> 00:18:28,600
[SIGHS]

337
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:30,667
Sir Fred too...

338
00:18:32,767 --> 00:18:34,000
It's a shame, isn't it?

339
00:18:34,667 --> 00:18:37,167
There are so many "What if's..."

340
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:39,567
But...

341
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:41,567
That's it. It already happened.

342
00:18:41,567 --> 00:18:44,500
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

343
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,967
[SIGHS]

344
00:18:49,033 --> 00:18:51,667
Didn't the police ask
for your statement, too?

345
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,567
Yes, sir.

346
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:55,833
I just remembered.

347
00:18:56,567 --> 00:18:59,167
You said you saw
a folder when Uncle Mike left.

348
00:19:00,067 --> 00:19:03,567
Ah, yes. I just told it
to Sir Henry recently.

349
00:19:03,567 --> 00:19:05,900
But yes, sir...
Sir Mike did carry a folder.

350
00:19:06,467 --> 00:19:08,067
But it wasn't
at the crime scene.

351
00:19:08,867 --> 00:19:12,000
That's it.
But we're so sure about it.

352
00:19:12,733 --> 00:19:14,167
Maybe it's with Roi?

353
00:19:14,767 --> 00:19:16,000
I don't think so.

354
00:19:16,433 --> 00:19:18,700
Roi insisted he had
nothing to do with it.

355
00:19:19,433 --> 00:19:22,567
Every criminal
denies it at first.

356
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:24,567
But do you know
what's in the folder?

357
00:19:24,567 --> 00:19:26,600
Or who is it from?

358
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:30,067
Not really, sir.

359
00:19:30,067 --> 00:19:33,500
It just says outside
that it was confidential.

360
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:36,700
The courier just handed it over,
but I'm sure it was Sir Mike's.

361
00:19:38,667 --> 00:19:42,200
It just made me wonder
what was in it.

362
00:19:43,733 --> 00:19:46,667
We need to make Roi confess.

363
00:19:46,667 --> 00:19:48,967
He was the only
one who could take it.

364
00:19:48,967 --> 00:19:51,633
Even Sir Henry couldn't find it.

365
00:19:51,633 --> 00:19:52,967
You're right.

366
00:19:52,967 --> 00:19:55,067
He deserves to be bitten
by a thousand ants.

367
00:19:55,067 --> 00:19:56,767
You're right.

368
00:19:56,767 --> 00:19:58,933
He caused a huge mess.

369
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:01,833
He changed their entire
lives.

370
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:08,900
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

371
00:20:11,267 --> 00:20:13,500
Okay.
I'm on my way there.

372
00:20:15,167 --> 00:20:16,867
Let's talk when
I get there.

373
00:20:16,867 --> 00:20:23,900
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

374
00:20:25,033 --> 00:20:28,233
I'm going to unearth everything
<i> you Almazans are hiding.</i>

375
00:20:32,533 --> 00:20:39,500
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

376
00:20:52,633 --> 00:20:54,967
[JUSTIN] Alright, bro...
I'm heading out.

377
00:20:57,867 --> 00:20:59,033
Leon?

378
00:21:00,033 --> 00:21:02,967
[PHONE RINGING]

379
00:21:04,167 --> 00:21:07,033
Justin, is there a problem?
I'm a bit busy.

380
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:08,533
Leon, I just saw--

381
00:21:08,567 --> 00:21:10,200
<i>I have a lot of work
in the office right now.</i>

382
00:21:12,367 --> 00:21:13,900
Office?

383
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:15,667
Yes. What is it?

384
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:17,700
[SCOFFS]

385
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:19,167
I thought you were at the hotel.

386
00:21:19,767 --> 00:21:22,000
I'm not there. Why?

387
00:21:24,733 --> 00:21:26,967
No, never mind, Leon. Bye.

388
00:21:30,267 --> 00:21:32,300
[SIGHS]

389
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,367
Why are you lying, Leon?

390
00:21:37,367 --> 00:21:44,333
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

391
00:21:48,967 --> 00:21:50,900
What is it, bro?
Why are you making such a fuss?

392
00:21:51,067 --> 00:21:51,933
What did Sari's grandfather say?

393
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:53,500
He said we can't tell anyone.

394
00:21:53,767 --> 00:21:54,867
Yes!

395
00:21:54,967 --> 00:21:56,867
You're following
instructions now.

396
00:21:56,967 --> 00:21:58,567
You believe now, don't you?

397
00:21:58,700 --> 00:21:59,900
- Not really.
- Huh?

398
00:22:00,933 --> 00:22:02,533
- Really?
- Just a bit.

399
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:05,500
I'm just doing this for Jade.

400
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:06,533
Fair point.

401
00:22:07,033 --> 00:22:09,600
But I've read something
on the internet, bro.

402
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:13,733
It is said that if the ritual
to remove your misfortune

403
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:16,200
- has been done properly...
- What then?

404
00:22:16,333 --> 00:22:18,900
Then the opposite
will come back.

405
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:22,400
So, we're going
to be lucky then, right?

406
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:24,067
That's not all.

407
00:22:24,167 --> 00:22:26,067
What I've read was that...

408
00:22:26,167 --> 00:22:28,267
a connection will come to you.

409
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:31,200
You didn't ask for it
but it's destined.

410
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:34,533
And when it comes, it's like...

411
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:37,467
You'll just feel
your heart pounding, you know.

412
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:41,600
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

413
00:22:41,733 --> 00:22:42,867
[CHESKA] Oh!

414
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:45,200
You believe it now, don't you?

415
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:46,133
Did you feel it?

416
00:22:46,300 --> 00:22:47,633
You felt it, didn't you?

417
00:22:47,767 --> 00:22:49,733
Whatever, you talk too much.

418
00:22:49,867 --> 00:22:50,667
- Hmph!
- Ouch!

419
00:22:50,833 --> 00:22:53,233
-Your heart felt it, didn't you?
- Nope!

420
00:22:53,367 --> 00:22:56,067
- Let me see your heart pound!
- Just leave your brother alone.

421
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:58,133
[CHESKA] Okay, I'll let it go.

422
00:22:58,267 --> 00:23:00,667
- One more? One more?
- There you go again.

423
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,767
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

424
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:03,933
Excuse me.

425
00:23:04,033 --> 00:23:05,467
Oh! Hello, ma'am.

426
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:07,167
Excuse me, I just checked in.

427
00:23:07,333 --> 00:23:08,767
I just have a question.

428
00:23:08,867 --> 00:23:10,233
Oh, yes. What is it?

429
00:23:10,433 --> 00:23:13,167
Do you have any
special requests, Miss...?

430
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:14,067
Maria.

431
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:16,733
- Miss Maria.
- Just call me Maria.

432
00:23:16,833 --> 00:23:20,100
Do you offer private tours?

433
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:23,167
I need a companion
from morning to night.

434
00:23:23,367 --> 00:23:24,633
Ah, a private tour?

435
00:23:24,733 --> 00:23:27,300
Yes, of course! We have those.
Just in time.

436
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:29,700
- Sir Justin will handle it.
- Hey, he said Justin!

437
00:23:29,833 --> 00:23:31,267
He called your name.

438
00:23:31,367 --> 00:23:34,100
- What do you need?
- The guest, she needs you.

439
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:37,433
Sir Justin is in charge
of recreational activities.

440
00:23:37,533 --> 00:23:40,633
Sir, our guest needs a companion
from morning to night.

441
00:23:41,833 --> 00:23:43,500
Morning to night?

442
00:23:43,667 --> 00:23:44,600
Sure.

443
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:46,767
We can arrange something.

444
00:23:46,867 --> 00:23:48,500
Is he the only one available?

445
00:23:48,667 --> 00:23:50,633
I mean, he's a guy.

446
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:51,967
I don't mean it that way, but--

447
00:23:52,067 --> 00:23:53,133
Oh, I understand!

448
00:23:53,233 --> 00:23:55,300
Do you feel uncomfortable
with just one companion?

449
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:57,333
- We also have Miss Cheska.
- Hey!

450
00:23:57,433 --> 00:23:59,300
- She'll also come with.
- What are you saying?

451
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,833
Why did I suddenly
get dragged in?

452
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,400
You should've fixed
how you look!

453
00:24:02,733 --> 00:24:05,533
Why me?
Would you like to go with me?

454
00:24:05,900 --> 00:24:07,967
She's also free.
You'll also come, right?

455
00:24:08,067 --> 00:24:10,333
- Yes, I would love to.
- Right!

456
00:24:11,033 --> 00:24:12,133
[TRIXIE] Wait a minute.

457
00:24:12,233 --> 00:24:14,967
Mom, I'll call you back.
Bye for now.

458
00:24:15,067 --> 00:24:16,900
- Cheska, what is this?
- Hmm?

459
00:24:17,033 --> 00:24:18,667
[BROODING MUSIC PLAYING]

460
00:24:18,767 --> 00:24:21,000
Welcome to Hotel 88!

461
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:22,167
Yes.

462
00:24:22,333 --> 00:24:25,367
The hotel that will
force you to participate.

463
00:24:26,533 --> 00:24:27,633
Welcome!

464
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:34,200
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

465
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:36,033
<i>- Hey! Energy!
- Ah!</i>

466
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:37,400
<i> We have a guest!</i>

467
00:24:37,567 --> 00:24:39,867
<i>- Is that what you'll wear?
- For island hopping?</i>

468
00:24:40,033 --> 00:24:41,833
<i>Who told you we'd go
island-hopping?</i>

469
00:24:41,933 --> 00:24:43,400
<i> Is that Jade?</i>

470
00:24:43,867 --> 00:24:45,233
<i>Is that why you can't
be serious about her?</i>

471
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,367
<i> Because she has a boyfriend?</i>

472
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:48,533
<i> Is there a ritual that...</i>

473
00:24:48,633 --> 00:24:50,867
will make me Sir Martin's date?

474
00:24:50,933 --> 00:24:52,433
<i>Because this is
a personal meeting!</i>

475
00:24:52,567 --> 00:24:54,367
<i>Promise me that
you won't tell anyone else.</i>

476
00:24:54,467 --> 00:24:56,033
<i> Solenn?</i>

477
00:24:56,467 --> 00:25:00,167
<i>With so many hotels out there,
why is Peter's friend here?</i>

